					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Portions of the inscription are lost. It seems to record a gift of land to the temple at Pēriṅgūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Pēriṅgūr-nāḍu of Tirumuṉaipāḍi, a division of Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻamaṇḍalam by a cavalry man (name not clear) of the commander (<hi rend="italic">Sēnāpati</hi>) Rājē[ndraśōḻa]-Brahmamārāyar, who got it exempted from tax by payment of a lump-sum to the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of the place.</p>						

						</summary>
